FBIS4-13301 "drnes075_s_94002" FBIS-NES-94-075 Daily Report 19 Apr 1994 Iran Iraqi `Saboteurs' Blamed Iraqi `Saboteurs' Blamed LD1904102794 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran First Program Network in Persian 0930 GMT 19 Apr 94 LD1904102794 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran First Program Network Persian BFN [Text] The explosion of a bomb in the vicinity of Tehran's Sa'di Avenue caused some damage today. According to the Central News Unit, the bomb was apparently planted inside a car that was parked under Sa'di Bridge. As a result of the explosion, one vehicle was destroyed, a number of passing vehicles suffered some damage, and the windows of several shops were broken. Fortunately, the incident did not cause any deaths. According to witnesses, a number of passersby were injured in the incident. Reliable security sources have announced: The Iraqi regime has recently sent four persons to Iran plant bombs for the purpose of sabotage, and today's explosion was caused by these same saboteurs.
